<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1890-08-07T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1890-08-07T00:00:00-05:00" n="55" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d55">
                    <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Wharton</persName> to Mr.
                                <persName type="to">Mizner</persName></hi>.</head>
                    <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg></opener>
                    <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department
                                    of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1890-08-07"><hi rend="italic">August</hi> 7,
                            1890</date>.</dateline></opener>
                    <p>Mr. Wharton informs Mr. Mizner that General Guirala has telegraphed that
                        messages from the Department to Mr. Mizner are not detained in Salvador. Mr.
                        Wharton adds that the detention would appear to be in Guatemalan territory,
                        and instructs Mr. Mizner to be watchful in that direction.</p>
                </div>
                </body></text></TEI>